<section id="intro">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Ever wondered how much a bushel of wheat weighs? You're in the right place.
        A bushel is a traditional unit used in agriculture, and for wheat, it has a
        standard weight that helps farmers and traders worldwide.
    </p>
</section>

<section id="weight">
    <h2>Standard Weight</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <h3>✔ Official Weight</h3>
        <p>1 bushel of wheat = <strong>60 pounds</strong> (~27.2 kg)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>📊 Quick Conversion</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>60 lbs</li>
            <li>27.2 kg</li>
            <li>960 ounces</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

